More at montblanc.com

Watch the second #MontblancSigned episode on IGTV or go to montblanc.com for more.

node.text:
We celebrated the launch of our latest collaboration by live
streaming with @matveimusic. Watch the full video at montblancxmaisonkitsune.com .

Created in Paris in 2002 by Gildas Loaëc and Masaya Kuroki, Kitsuné offers a unique Art de Vivre blending a fashion brand @maisonkitsune, music label @kitsunemusique and cafés, bars and restaurants @cafekitsune. “Kitsuné”, the Japanese word for “fox”, is a symbol of versatility that according to legend possesses the power to change its appearance. With this new collaboration, their next shape-shifting act is revealed. 
  
Shop the drop montblanc.com

node.text:
Thinking about founding a start-up?
We might have something for you: #RaisingTheStakes, the first episode of our new series #MontblancSigned.
A journey to the early days of a start-up you today might know under the name “Montblanc”.

Watch the first #MontblancSigned episode on IGTV or go to montblanc.com for more.

#CillianMurphy’s first experiences on the stage were with a guitar by his side, playing in a rock band alongside his brother. At age 19, he began following another of his passions: acting. Whether playing a survivor of a zombie apocalypse or the swaggering leader of a Birmingham criminal gang, Murphy leaves a mark in the minds of audiences by approaching each new role with audacity and creativity.

We’re proud to welcome him as our Montblanc Mark Maker. #WhatMovesYouMakesYou

node.text:
Sometimes, changing just one small thing makes a huge impact. For @peggygou_, eating healthier made her think clearer and work better towards her passions.

Making a conscious decision to change something takes courage, and sometimes it also requires persistence and patience. But if it means moving in the right direction, we're here for it. #WhatMovesYouMakesYou

node.text:
Forever switching between countries, venues and sets, @peggygou_ never stands still for long. And all that movement requires accessories that keep up.

We designed the Montblanc Ultra Black Clutch for people — like Gou — who are always on the move. Select your essentials, sling it over a shoulder and get going. What's your next destination?

"Something should move you to be better, to do better. If you don't feel that, you're in the safe zone", @peggygou_ told us.
We couldn't agree more. 

Watch the full video to hear more from our new Montblanc Mark Maker. #WhatMovesYouMakesYou

node.text:
@peggygou_ has DJ'ed at some of the biggest venues worldwide, released multiple successful LPs and launched her record label, Gudu records. She's forging her own path to success, and it's a path filled with music.

We each have our own personal connection with music. For some, it's a source of inspiration; for others, it's a form of expression. Whichever it is for you, our wireless MB01 Headphones offer a cutting-edge sound experience for connecting with the music that moves you. Tap to shop.

node.text:
We're thrilled to introduce you to our Montblanc Mark Maker: #PeggyGou.

@peggygou_ knows what it is to move where your passions take you — both on the dancefloor and in life. Originally from South Korea, she studied fashion in London and later worked there as a correspondent fashion editor. Then, to her other passion — music — she moved to Berlin. Since then, she's played at some of the most prestigious venues and festivals worldwide. Her success and popularity haven't been a lucky break. It's the result of a relentless drive towards the things that move her. #WhatMovesYouMakesYou
